From 81366298b6634d9b30fe3973ad15e9126f96678c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: regksem <regksem@tuta.io>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 14:07:35 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Add runtime plugin management and the /manager command

Adds a PlugMan-style /manager command (alias /plugman) to load, unload, reload,
enable, disable and inspect plugins and modules at runtime, backed by new
PluginManager API: loadPlugin(File), unloadPlugin/reloadPlugin/disablePlugin/
enablePlugin(Plugin) and isPluginEnabled(Plugin).

Unloading disables the plugin, cancels its scheduled tasks, shuts down its
executor, unregisters its commands and listeners, drops it from the dependency
graph and closes its class loader. PluginClassloader.close() now also removes
itself from the shared loader set so an unloaded plugin's classes stop resolving
for other plugins, and Plugin gains a package-private shutdownExecutorService().

